e centrality of territory to modern states and the consequences of legal categorizations of race and ethnicity. Though focused on Afro-Colombian struggles for political space in their country, Turf Wars also illustrates how these struggles are part of events and entities operating on a much broader global front.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aBlack peoplexLand tenurezColombia. 0aBlack peoplezColombiaxClaims. 0aBlack peoplezColombiaxGovernment relations. 4aAnthropology -- Political and Legal Anthropology. 4aLatin American Studies. 4aSociology -- Social Movements, Civil Society, and Politics. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertStanford University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831107042040 cprintz978080475596240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780804768290?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804768290423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780804768290/original  a978-3-11-070420-4  Stanford University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles